 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Media Player With Full Caption Support\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated perspectives confirmed\n\nFrom the a11y-critic escalation:\n\n- **Auditory Access \u2014 MEDIUM** \u2192 deep review\n- **Screen Reader & Semantic Structure \u2014 MEDIUM** \u2192 deep review\n\nNot escalated (LOW / not reviewed): Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Keyboard & Motor Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent.\n\nScope note from the fixture context: the page shell supplies `<html lang=\"en\">`, `<title>Tutorial | Acme Corp</title>`, and the `<main>` landmark. Page-level criteria (2.4.2 title, 3.1.1 html lang, 1.3.1 main landmark) are therefore reviewed as **out of component scope**, not as component failures.\n\nIncoming contract carries plain alarm levels only \u2014 no `A11y Evidence Finding` block, no `keyboard-a11y-tester` journey trace, and no `virtual-screen-reader` phrase log. There are no upstream finding_ids/fingerprints/trace-step citations to preserve.\n\n---\n\n## Step 4 \u2014 Per-perspective checklists\n\n### Perspective 4 \u2014 Auditory Access\n\nWCAG (AA): 1.2.1, 1.2.2, 1.2.3, 1.2.5, 1.4.2\n\n**Code-level checklist (enforceable from source):**\n\n| # | Item | Result | Evidence |\n|---|------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | `<video>` with speech has `<track kind=\"captions\">` with valid `src` (1.2.2) | **PASS** | Line 75 \u2014 `<track kind=\"captions\" src=\"/video/tutorial-en.vtt\" srcLang=\"en\" label=\"English captions\" default />`. `default` sets the track showing on load, and `captionsOn` initializes to `true` (line 27), so announced state and rendered state agree. |\n| 2 | Every `<audio>` has adjacent transcript/link (1.2.1) | **N/A** | No `<audio>` element. Content is a captioned `<video>` with synchronized audio, so 1.2.1 (audio-only / video-only) does not apply. A full transcript is present regardless (lines 119\u2013128). |\n| 3 | Player controls (play, pause, volume, caption toggle) keyboard-operable (2.1.1) | **PASS** | Controls are native `<button>` (lines 81, 114) and `<input type=\"range\">` (lines 86, 102). Native elements are keyboard-operable by default: Space/Enter on buttons, arrows/Home/End on ranges. |\n| 4 | Visual indicators accompany auditory alerts | **N/A** | Component emits no auditory alerts/notifications. |\n| 5 | No audio auto-plays, or auto-play has immediate stop in first focusable element (1.4.2) | **PASS** | `autoPlay={false}` (line 70); `preload=\"metadata\"` loads metadata only, no playback. |\n\nNo auto-CRITICAL red flag fires: captions track is present (not \"video with speech and no track\"), controls are keyboard-operable (not \"no keyboard controls\"), and there is no autoplay (not \"audio auto-plays with no stop control\").\n\n**Content-level checklist (human verification \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source):**\n\n| # | Item | Result |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 6 | Caption accuracy and timing (1.2.2) | Infrastructure present; `.vtt` content not readable from source \u2192 **verify** |\n| 7 | Transcript includes speaker identification (1.2.1/1.2.3) | Single-narrator tutorial; timestamps present (lines 122\u2013126), explicit speaker ID not required for one voice \u2192 **verify** |\n| 8 | Audio descriptions cover visual-only information (1.2.3, 1.2.5) | `<track kind=\"descriptions\">` present (line 76) \u2014 1.2.5 (AA) infrastructure is in place; whether the description track's content covers on-screen-only actions is not readable from source \u2192 **verify** |\n\nNote on 1.2.3 vs 1.2.5: the transcript (`<details>`) satisfies the 1.2.3 (Level A) media-alternative requirement. 1.2.5 (Level AA) additionally requires audio description specifically \u2014 a transcript alone does **not** discharge it. The `kind=\"descriptions\"` track is the correct code-level answer to 1.2.5, so the component is architecturally complete for AA. This is a screencast whose narration already verbalizes most actions (\"navigate to the Dashboard and click New Project\u2026\"), which reduces \u2014 but does not eliminate \u2014 the audio-description burden. Content completeness remains a human check.\n\n**Auditory Access verdict:** All code-level items PASS or N/A. No CRITICAL/MAJOR. Remaining items are content-verification, not confirmed defects.\n\n---\n\n### Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n\nWCAG (AA): 1.1.1, 1.3.1, 1.3.2, 2.4.2, 2.4.4, 2.4.6, 3.1.1, 3.1.2, 3.3.1, 3.3.2, 4.1.2, 4.1.3\n\n| # | Item | Result | Evidence |\n|---|------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Landmark regions present and correct (1.3.1) | **PASS** (scope) | `<section aria-label=\"Video player\">` (line 57) exposes a named `region` landmark; `<main>` is supplied by the shell. Appropriate component-level containment. |\n| 2 | Logical heading hierarchy, headings describe content (2.4.6) | **PASS** (scope) | `<h2>Tutorial: Getting Started</h2>` (line 58) is descriptive and sits correctly one level below the shell's `<h1>`. |\n| 3 | Informative images have descriptive `alt`; decorative `alt=\"\"` (1.1.1) | **PASS** | No `<img>` elements. `poster=\"/img/tutorial-poster.jpg\"` (line 65) is a video poster (no alt slot; video is not the accessible-name source here). Button glyphs `\u25b6 \u23f8 CC` sit inside buttons whose `aria-label` overrides the visible text for the accessible name, so the glyphs are effectively decorative. |\n| 4 | DOM/source order matches visual reading order (1.3.2) | **PASS** | Source order: heading \u2192 video \u2192 controls (play, seek, time, volume, CC) \u2192 transcript. Matches the visual/interaction order. |\n| 5 | Unique descriptive `<title>` (2.4.2) | **N/A** (scope) | Provided by shell. |\n| 6 | Link text describes destination (2.4.4) | **N/A** | No links in component. |\n| 7 | `lang` on `<html>` (3.1.1) | **N/A** (scope) | Provided by shell (`<html lang=\"en\">`). |\n| 8 | Foreign-language phrases wrapped in `lang` (3.1.2) | **N/A** | No foreign-language content. |\n| 9 | Every input has programmatically associated label (3.3.2) | **PASS** | Seek input `id=\"seek-slider\"` paired with `<label htmlFor=\"seek-slider\">` (lines 85\u201387) plus `aria-label`; volume input `id=\"volume-slider\"` paired with `<label htmlFor=\"volume-slider\">` (lines 101\u2013103) plus `aria-label`. Every control has an accessible name. |\n| 10 | Error messages identify field, associated via `aria-describedby` (3.3.1) | **N/A** | No form errors in component. |\n| 11 | Custom widgets use correct ARIA roles matching APG (4.1.2) | **FINDING (MINOR)** | `role=\"toolbar\"` (line 80) does not implement the APG toolbar roving-tabindex / arrow-key pattern. See Finding SR-1. Buttons use `aria-pressed` correctly (line 114); sliders use `aria-valuetext` correctly. |\n| 12 | Status messages use `aria-live` with appropriate urgency (4.1.3) | **PASS** | `time-display` carries `aria-live=\"off\"` (line 97) \u2014 correctly suppressing what would otherwise be a per-frame time flood. Play/pause state rides the button's dynamic `aria-label` (line 81); caption state rides `aria-pressed` (line 114); slider values ride native value announcement + `aria-valuetext`. No missing live region. |\n| 13 | SPA route changes managed | **N/A** | No route changes in component. |\n\nSecondary observation under 3.3.2 / 4.1.2 \u2192 Finding SR-2 (redundant slider naming).\n\nNo auto-CRITICAL red flag fires: `<main>` handled by shell; no unlabeled inputs; no custom widget without a role; `html lang` handled by shell.\n\n**Screen Reader verdict:** No CRITICAL/MAJOR. Two MINOR polish findings below.\n\n---\n\n## Step 5 \u2014 Findings\n\n**Finding SR-1:** `role=\"toolbar\"` is applied to the controls container but the APG toolbar keyboard pattern (single Tab stop into the group, Left/Right Arrow to move between controls via roving tabindex) is not implemented \u2014 every control is an independent Tab stop.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** Line 80 \u2014 `<div className=\"player-controls\" role=\"toolbar\" aria-label=\"Video controls\">`. No `onKeyDown` arrow handling and no `tabIndex` management on the child controls; native buttons/inputs each remain natively focusable.\n**Fix:** Two defensible paths \u2014 (a) keep independent tab stops and downgrade the container to `role=\"group\"` with the same `aria-label`, which advertises grouping without promising arrow-key navigation the widget doesn't provide; or (b) retain `role=\"toolbar\"` and accept the deviation. Do **not** naively add roving-tabindex arrow navigation: the toolbar contains two `<input type=\"range\">` sliders that already consume Left/Right/Up/Down arrows for value adjustment, so arrow-based inter-control navigation would collide with slider operation. Given the sliders, individual tab stops are the reasonable choice and `role=\"group\"` is the cleaner label for it. This does not block any user \u2014 the `aria-label=\"Video controls\"` grouping is announced and every control is reachable and operable.\n\n**Finding SR-2:** Both sliders duplicate the time/volume value across `aria-label` and `aria-valuetext`, producing a doubled announcement.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (also touches 3.3.2 Labels)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** Seek slider (lines 93\u201394) \u2014 `aria-label={`Seek: ${formatTime(currentTime)} of ${formatTime(duration)}`}` **and** `aria-valuetext={`${formatTime(currentTime)} of ${formatTime(duration)}`}`. Volume slider (lines 110\u2013111) \u2014 `aria-label={`Volume: ${Math.round(volume*100)}%`}` **and** `aria-valuetext={`${Math.round(volume*100)}%`}`. A screen reader announces name + value, so the seek slider reads roughly \"Seek: 0:15 of 1:00, slider, 0:15 of 1:00\" \u2014 the value is spoken twice, and the label mutates on every tick.\n**Fix:** Make `aria-label` the static purpose only (`\"Seek\"`, `\"Volume\"`) and let the changing value live solely in `aria-valuetext`. The accessible name then stays stable while the value updates, eliminating the double read. This is a verbosity refinement, not a barrier \u2014 all information is currently conveyed.\n\n**Content-level flags (Auditory Access) \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source:**\n\n**Finding AUD-C1:** Caption accuracy, timing, and synchronization unverifiable from markup.\n**WCAG:** 1.2.2 Captions (Prerecorded)\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** Not scored \u2014 verification item (infrastructure PASS; content unconfirmable)\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `/video/tutorial-en.vtt` referenced (line 75) but the cue file is not part of the reviewed source.\n**Fix:** Human review of the `.vtt` for verbatim accuracy, correct timing, and inclusion of relevant non-speech audio. `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n**Finding AUD-C2:** Audio-description track content coverage unverifiable from markup.\n**WCAG:** 1.2.5 Audio Description (Prerecorded)\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** Not scored \u2014 verification item (1.2.5 infrastructure PASS via `kind=\"descriptions\"`; content unconfirmable)\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `<track kind=\"descriptions\" src=\"/video/tutorial-desc.vtt\" \u2026>` present (line 76); cue content not in source. Note also that browser rendering of `kind=\"descriptions\"` tracks is uneven, so confirm the delivery mechanism actually surfaces the descriptions to AT in target browsers.\n**Fix:** Human review confirming the description cues narrate visual-only information (on-screen clicks, UI locations) not covered by the primary narration; verify AT actually receives them. `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n**Finding AUD-C3:** Transcript completeness / speaker attribution.\n**WCAG:** 1.2.1 / 1.2.3\n**Perspective:** Auditory Access\n**Severity:** Not scored \u2014 verification item (transcript present with timestamps)\n**Route to:** Content Author\n**Evidence:** Transcript in `<details>` (lines 119\u2013128) covers 0:00\u20131:00 with timestamps; single narrator, so speaker labels are not required, but full coverage of the finished video's runtime should be confirmed.\n**Fix:** Confirm the transcript matches the shipped video end-to-end. `[Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]`\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** Media Player With Full Caption Support (React `MediaPlayer`)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Auditory Access (MEDIUM), Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Keyboard & Motor Access, Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 0 |\n| MAJOR | 0 |\n| MINOR | 2 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 0 |\n\n(Plus 3 content-level verification items, AUD-C1\u2013C3, not severity-scored because the infrastructure passes at code level and the content cannot be confirmed from source.)\n\n### Perspectives That Passed (code level)\n\n- **Auditory Access** \u2014 every code-level checklist item PASS or N/A. Captions track with `default`, keyboard-operable native controls, no autoplay, audio-description track present, and a timestamped transcript. Only content-authoring verification remains; no code defect.\n- **Screen Reader & Semantic Structure** \u2014 clears the CRITICAL/MAJOR bar. Correct region landmark, descriptive heading, native labeled controls, correct `aria-pressed`, and a deliberately correct `aria-live=\"off\"` on the ticking time display. Two MINOR polish items only.\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- `role=\"toolbar\"` without APG roving-tabindex pattern (SR-1) \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MINOR \u2014 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n- Redundant `aria-label` + `aria-valuetext` value duplication on both sliders (SR-2) \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MINOR \u2014 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n\n**Content Author**\n- Caption accuracy/timing verification (AUD-C1) \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 verification \u2014 1.2.2\n- Audio-description content coverage + AT delivery verification (AUD-C2) \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 verification \u2014 1.2.5\n- Transcript full-runtime coverage (AUD-C3) \u2014 Auditory Access \u2014 verification \u2014 1.2.1/1.2.3\n\n**Visual Design** \u2014 none.\n**UX Design** \u2014 none (secondary on SR-1: choose `group` vs `toolbar` semantics).\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n1. **Caption fidelity** \u2014 Is `/video/tutorial-en.vtt` verbatim, correctly timed, and inclusive of meaningful non-speech audio? (1.2.2)\n2. **Audio-description coverage** \u2014 Does `/video/tutorial-desc.vtt` narrate on-screen-only actions the primary narration skips, and does the target browser/AT stack actually surface a `kind=\"descriptions\"` track? (1.2.5)\n3. **Transcript completeness** \u2014 Does the `<details>` transcript cover the full shipped runtime (not just the first 1:00 shown)? (1.2.1/1.2.3)\n\nNone of these is a confirmed defect; each is an inherent boundary of source-only review. They should be closed by a content author before final sign-off.\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**PASS** \u2014 no CRITICAL or MAJOR findings. The component is architecturally complete for AA on both escalated perspectives: captions, transcript, audio-description infrastructure, keyboard-operable native controls, correct live-region suppression, and labeled widgets are all in place. Address the two MINOR polish items (SR-1 `toolbar` semantics, SR-2 slider announcement redundancy) opportunistically \u2014 neither blocks shipping. Close the three content-verification questions (AUD-C1\u2013C3) with a content author before publishing the video, since caption/description *content* quality is the one thing source review cannot certify.\n",
